   "source": [
    "### 1. Create a set from a list\n",
    "**Return:** A set containing unique elements from the list"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "id": "ead4f135",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{2, 3, 4, 5}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 35,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def list_to_set(lst: list) -> set:\n",
    "   return set(lst)\n",
    "list_to_set([2,3,4,5,5])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "223e4bc3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Remove a specific element from a list\n",
    "**Return:** The list after removing the first occurrence of the element"
